Canadian LNG Projects

Erica Beattie

The global liquified natural gas (LNG) market is poised to grow dramatically, with drastic increases in prices and demand creating optimism among suppliers.

Gas and LNG Prices Increases in 2021

LNG presents a great opportunity for Canada, with Shells LNG Canada project under construction, Woodfibre LNG beginning construction, and a major expansion of LNG Canada plant under consideration.

Shell LNG Outlook

Major current events such as the COVID-19 pandemic and Russias war on Ukraine have had tremendous impacts on the demand for LNG, further proving the importance of Canadas role in the LNG industry. By exporting LNG, especially to Asia, Canada can help significantly in lowering global emissions. The world is beginning to understand the importance of not only natural energy, but clean energy, and they are also worried about where to source this energy from. This is where the Woodfibre LNG project and its exceptionaly low emissions can make a crucial difference.

Canadian LNG is in incredibly high demand due to its responsibility, sustainability, and stability. A supply-demand gap for LNG is expected to emerge, giving all the more reason to encourage Canadian projects such as Woodfibre in the near future.
